10:36.280 --> 10:39.760
So what is cart context provider doing for us?

10:39.760 --> 10:40.640
Well, the first thing is that

10:40.640 --> 10:42.680
that can be kind of strange with React.

10:42.680 --> 10:44.000
You can have components that

10:44.000 --> 10:45.960
don't actually render real markup.

10:45.960 --> 10:47.640
All they do is they act as kind of a pass-through,

10:47.640 --> 10:48.960
but they augment the ability

10:48.960 --> 10:50.960
of the components inside of them.

10:50.960 --> 10:52.320
And that's what this provider is doing.

10:52.320 --> 10:54.920
It's now making whatever value

10:54.920 --> 10:55.880
that we're gonna pass into it,

10:55.880 --> 10:58.960
which we'll do momentarily, we have not done yet.

10:58.960 --> 11:02.400
